Text.Value: Aw, don't be so hard on him. With his daddy issues and all, he's had a rough go.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Talking to player, then to Wyll.
An infernal rune appears on the ground beneath Mizora exits in.

Text.Value: Connect your mind to the 'annihilate' device and activate it.
Gather your strength and smash your foot through the pod.
But don't you fret. If you survive this place, I'll find you. The pup will be needing me. Count on it.
Free Wyll, or I let the cult infect you. I bet you'd make a loyal thrall.
*Your eyes turn to the control panel next to the pod. It has two devices marked with illithid symbols.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The player turns their attention to the console that controls the pod.

Text.Value: Clause Z, Section Thirteen: 'If the soul-binder consents to separation, she will release the soul-bearer from all obligation within six months.'

EditorData.NodeContext: Sound effect on voice. Something heightened, like Galadriel in lord of the rings when she goes nuts.

Text.Value: Six months? Are nine Hells so few that you would make our lives a tenth?
Good work. I'd give you a gold star, but I'm fresh out.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Mizora steps out of the pod and leaps down

Text.Value: Damnation at the flick of a switch. You cast your allies aside easily.

EditorData.NodeContext: Disdain, but no blame. We've just damned a companion to the hells, and it reminds her of how easily she cast her own friend aside. She dislikes us as much as she dislikes herself.

Text.Value: Now open the pod.
My sparkling disposition will more than suffice.
And you thought that idiotic display would do it? Bravo!
That warlock of yours is turning out to be more trouble than he's worth.
Thought you'd have figured it out before now.
*You recognise the marking from the nautiloid: an illithid symbol meaning 'unleash'.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: [GERRY] The player's fist slams against the pod but it remains intact.
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: [reuse] The player's fist slams against the pod but it remains intact.
EditorData.SFXTags: [KrisB] Player runs up and kicks the pod

Text.Value: Now enough sniffing around and get me out of this thing.
Poor thing. I'll let you out of there.
Dead serious. Don't let the smile fool you.
*You recall an old incantation from a children's story, said to void a devil's contract: 'Abi, diabole, et nunquam redi.'*
*You can think of no way to void a devil's pact.*
By Graz'zt's cock, it's about time you came.

EditorData.NodeContext: Graz-its cock (quite a swear indeed). Said with only the slightest urgency. Mizora should still sound her confident self, even with her trapped inside the pod

Text.Value: The limpet clings on. Young Wyll had parasite problems well before the tadpole, it seems.

EditorData.NodeContext: Utter amused scorn for Mizora and all her kind - cambions are just parasites, clinging onto living souls

Text.Value: Fine, I'll play your game. But I amend the pact once I'm freed - not before.
All done? Good. Now enough sniffing around and get me out of this thing.
*You've heard of this provision - better known as the 'You First' clause.*
SMASH THE POD.
What have we here? Hold on - I need to relish the moment.
As for the pact: hrm. Mm-mm-mgh-AHEM.

EditorData.NodeContext: She gears up to read the contract, lots of self-please hemming and hawing leading up to it.

Text.Value: Wait... what? No. This can't be. Bring him back. Bring him back NOW!
*Mizora's life rests in your hands. Perhaps you could end Wyll's pact, here and now.*
*The Hells have taken Wyll as their own. He is lost to the fires of Avernus.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: [GERRY] The player's fist slams against the pod and it cracks open. Mizora leaps down, and spreads her wings, one after the other.
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext:
[reuse]  The player's fist slams against the pod and it cracks open.

Mizora steps out of the pod.
EditorData.SFXTags: [KrisB] Player runs up and kicks the pod

Text.Value: Don't take long. They pop a tadpole in me, and the Hells'll take Wyll for good.
Shrug. Six months isn't that long of a wait.
Mizora? You are the devil you sent Wyll to rescue?
Leave her there.
Gone. The Hells have claimed their prize.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [GERRY] The party approaches a mind flayer pod. Inside is the half-devil Mizora, Wyll's patron. She pushes her hands against the transparent cover and smiles. Next to the pod is a console with two buttons on it, the 'unleash' and 'annihilate' buttons on the console in the tutorial.
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The party approaches a mind flayer pod. Inside is the half-devil Mizora, Wyll's patron. She pushes her hands against the transparent cover and smiles. Next to the pod is a console with two buttons on it, the 'unleash' and 'annihilate' buttons on the console in the tutorial.

Text.Value: Not going to happen, but I do like your spunk.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Talking to player, then to Wyll.

Text.Value: Six months until he's free? You little rat.
Do it, and I'll let Wyll off his leash. A devil always keeps her promises.

EditorData.logicalname: Mizora agreed to free Wyll already

Text.Value: A bit of gratitude, then?
*You know this symbol from the mind flayer ship. It means 'annihilate'.*
*The controls are open to your tadpole's command - to your authority.*
Ignorant thing. It's always the terms and conditions that get you.
Incredible - you actually think you hold the winning hand.
Think again. Clause Z, Section Thirteen - the 'Lemure' clause. Could've sworn we covered this.
Connect your mind to the 'unleash' device and activate it.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [GERRY] Player presses the right-side button on the console. Mizora falls out, then gets to her feet. She unfolds one wing, and then the other.
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player presses the right-side button on the console. Mizora falls out, then gets to her feet.
EditorData.SFXTags: [KrisB] Mindmeld the pod to activate it
EditorData.VFXTags: [KrisB] Mindmeld the pod to activate it

Text.Value: 'Abi, diabole, et nunquam redi.'
You're a disgusting little shit, you know that, Mizora?
Six months is a trifle - you'd barely read through a single bookcase in Candlekeep in such a time.
Examine the device on the right.
You wouldn't want Wyll to get sucked into the Hells, would you?
Connect your mind to the device on the left and activate it.
It wasn't just her fate we decided... Wyll - he belongs to the Hells now.

EditorData.NodeContext: Regretful. A party member's been sent to hell, permanently.

Text.Value: Remember all you can about devils and their contracts.
*The symbol's meaning comes into focus: 'annihilate'.*
That's the best you've got?
Six months? We could be long dead before that long's elapsed.
Examine the device on the left.
Fine, let's get on with it.
*Your heart burns red-hot, then goes hollow. A presence disappears from your mind.*
Connect your mind to the device on the right and activate it.
A full half of a year? You've got to be kidding.
Go on and gloat, bow to your pretend crowd.
Me? I'm out of here. You? I don't play tarot.
You're free. What happens next?

EditorData.AnimationTags: [GERRY ]Mizora(REACTION) is sucked downwards from the pod. Blood splatters against the pod's window.
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: A psionic blast is released and Mizora is killed.
EditorData.SFXTags: [KrisB] Player presses the 'Annihilate' button, releasing a psionic blast within the pod, killing mizora and sucking her down the pod
EditorData.VFXTags: [KrisB] Player presses the 'Annihilate' button, releasing a psionic blast within the pod, killing mizora and sucking her down the pod

Text.Value: Right, I'm out of here - I need a long bath. I'll leave you to your very serious business.
Leave her there.
And you figured I'd be impressed by that little display? Heartbreaking.
She's gone... and Wyll's been consigned to the Hells along with her. Farewell, Blade.
Hells. What's happening? What have you -
Hells. They've taken the Blade to his final frontier.
Say you know a pact-breaking charm and chant a series of pseudo-Infernal phrases.
Playtime's over. Get me out.
Clause F, Section Nine: 'Soul-binder shall bestow reward or favour only upon soul-bearer's fulfilment of related obligation.'
Figures. All that talk about 'Zariel's asset', I should've known you were lying.
She's gone... and Wyll's been dragged to the Hells in her wake. Silvanus, keep his memory.
Six months? It can be done. A long life well lived will soon render it but a fleeting memory.
I've got half a mind to kill you where you stand.
*The button's symbol means nothing to you.*
Ha. Haha. Hahahahahaha!

EditorData.AnimationTags: [GERRY] Mizora in pod. Laughing hysterically that a player tried a children's incantation to release themselves from a devil's contract.
EditorData.NodeContext: Laughing hysterically that a player tried a children's incantation to release themselves from a devil's contract.

Text.Value: *You decipher the symbol: it's an illithid sigil meaning 'unleash'.*
To the Hells with your conditions. Sever Wyll's pact now, or I'll sever your head.
Why, perish the thought. Every word was nothing less than true.
I'll be damned. You want to free the pup from his pact.
*You can make no sense of the symbol.*
Oh, and ask Wyll how we met - I've loosened his tongue. It's a real cracker of a tale. Ta-ta!

Synopsis: Party finds Mizora in her pod in Moonrise Towers and chooses whether to release her or flush her down the tube. If alive, she flies off to wait for Wyll. Version for if Wyll is not in Party.
